AlphaPulse: Investment Risk & Volatility Monitor
AlphaPulse is a portfolio analytics solution developed to provide a comprehensive view of market risk and asset behavior for a multi-stock investment portfolio.
The project focuses on transforming raw financial data into actionable insights using quantitative risk metrics and visual analytics.
Historical stock price data was collected and cleaned, followed by the computation of key financial indicators such as daily returns, portfolio-level returns, and rolling volatility.
Prices were normalized to a base value to enable meaningful comparison across assets with different price scales, allowing clear visualization of relative performance trends.
To assess diversification and interdependencies between assets, a correlation matrix was generated and visualized as a heatmap, highlighting positive and negative relationships within the portfolio. 
This enables better allocation decisions and risk mitigation strategies.
A Monte Carlo simulation framework was implemented to model thousands of potential future portfolio paths based on historical return distributions. This probabilistic approach provides a forward-looking view of uncertainty and potential outcomes, supporting risk-aware decision-making.
The final output was integrated into an interactive Tableau dashboard, enabling dynamic exploration of price trends, volatility patterns, correlations, and simulated portfolio performance. The dashboard serves as a decision-support tool for understanding portfolio risk exposure and improving investment strategy.